# Experimental Data

This directory contains the experimental startup current signals used to validate the proposed analog fault detection method.

## Data Format

Each data file contains two columns:

| Column | Description                       |
| :----: | --------------------------------- |
|    1   | Time vector (s)                   |
|    2   | Normalized startup current (p.u.) |

## Sampling Information

* Sampling frequency: **23,404.4 Hz (23.4 kHz)**
* Sampling period: **42.727 us**

The time vector is uniformly sampled in all measurements.

## Rotor Conditions

* `Healthy` – Healthy rotor.
* `1_2_Bar` – Half broken bar.
* `1_Bar` – One broken bar.
* `2_Bars` – Two adjacent broken bars.
* `2_Bars_90` – Two broken bars separated by 90°.
* `2_Bars_180` – Two broken bars separated by 180°.

## Notes

The startup current was normalized since the experimental validation employed these normalized signals as the input to the function generator. These datasets were used to validate the proposed analog signal-conditioning circuit and the fault detection method presented in the associated paper.


